{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770319970,"nonce":"47AXosRYacmSSZ2D5QuZLeHK0sU=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87opnM3","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/170","origin":"github"},"title":"Auto-setup all layers from project layers.txt","message":"## Problem\n\nCurrently, when bootstrapping a new workspace, only the `core` layer is set up automatically. Other layers (including `underlay` which contains critical dependencies like geodesy) must be manually set up, leading to build failures.\n\n## Solution\n\nModify `setup.sh` to read `config/layers.txt` from the project repository and automatically set up all layers in the order specified.\n\n## Implementation\n\nAfter cloning the key repository during bootstrap:\n1. Read `layers/main/core_ws/src/unh_marine_autonomy/config/layers.txt`\n2. Loop through each layer and run setup for it\n3. Maintains proper dependency order (underlay before core, etc.)\n\n## Benefits\n\n- ✅ Workspace \"just works\" after bootstrap - all layers ready to build\n- ✅ Honors project-defined layer order\n- ✅ No manual intervention needed\n- ✅ Keeps .repos files separate (needed for Docker builds)","files":null}]}